	Go on, do it....

============================================================================
PLAYING FROM DISK:

	Simply copy all files to a disk and name it as "nsx"...
	and make the first line of your startup-sequence as: 

		nsx-free.exe

PLAYING FROM HARD DISK:

	Copy all files to a directory in your hard-drive. Add a line
	to your 'startup-sequence' or 'user-startup' as;

	ASSIGN "nsx:" <your directory name, with full path>

	change directory to where nsx is and run the file: nsx-free.exe
